ing-something-oftener-it-means/articleshow/131697814.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/quote-of-the-day-by-henry-ford-most-people-think-that-faith-means-believing-something-oftener-it-means/articleshow/131697814.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-13T18:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131698019,imgsize-24848.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Palestine Action activists jailed over raid on Israeli defence firm in UK; court cites 'terror connection' ]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131701134.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/raid-on-israeli-defence-firm-in-uk-4-palestine-action-activists-jailed-after-court-finds-terror-link/articleshow/131701134.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/raid-on-israeli-defence-firm-in-uk-4-palestine-action-activists-jailed-after-court-finds-terror-link/articleshow/131701134.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-13T14:50:15+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131701190,imgsize-131258.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[1,569 days and counting: Russia-Ukraine war now longer than World War I]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131697154.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The Russia-Ukraine war has surpassed World War I in duration, now exceeding 1,569 days. What began as a swift Russian operation has become Europe's longest and bloodiest conflict since WWII, defying early predictions. Despite diplomatic efforts and Western support for Ukraine, a durable peace remains elusive, with no clear end in sight.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/1569-days-and-counting-russia-ukraine-war-now-longer-than-world-war-i/articleshow/131697154.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/europe/1569-days-and-counting-russia-ukraine-war-now-longer-than-world-war-i/articleshow/131697154.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-13T09:10:52+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131697161,imgsize-1382675.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[From Lebanon ceasefire to nuclear talks: What are the terms proposed by Iran in 'Islamabad Agreement']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131696693.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Iran has outlined conditions for a potential US agreement, prioritizing sanctions relief and maritime access over immediate nuclear program discussions. Tehran insists on lifting the US naval blockade and a new arrangement for the Strait of Hormuz, while also seeking to include Lebanon in the deal.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/from-lebanon-ceasefire-to-nuclear-talks-what-are-the-terms-proposed-by-iran-in-islamabad-agreement/articleshow/131696693.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/from-lebanon-ceasefire-to-nuclear-talks-what-are-the-terms-proposed-by-iran-in-islamabad-agreement/articleshow/131696693.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-13T08:38:58+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131696953,imgsize-1024598.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Driven to London by masked men': Indian-origin man Gagandeep Singh sentenced to 34-years for kidnaping, raping woman]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131696224.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[An Indian-origin man, Gagandeep Singh, has been sentenced to 34 years in prison in the UK for kidnapping, torturing, and raping a woman. The 34-year-old was convicted of multiple serious offenses after a trial. He will serve 28 years in custody, followed by an extended license period, and will be deported after completing his sentence.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/nri/driven-to-london-by-masked-men-indian-origin-man-gagandeep-singh-sentenced-to-34-years-for-kidnaping-raping-woman/articleshow/131696224.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/nri/driven-to-london-by-masked-men-indian-origin-man-gagandeep-singh-sentenced-to-34-years-for-kidnaping-raping-woman/articleshow/131696224.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-13T07:30:36+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131696281,imgsize-290533.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Paraguay's president will be at USA's FIFA World Cup 2026 opener, but is Donald Trump attending?]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131696028.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[As the United States prepare to open their FIFA World Cup 2026 campaign against Paraguay, attention has shifted off the pitch after Paraguayan president Santiago Peña confirmed he will attend the match in Los Angeles while US president Donald Trump will not. Trump instead offered support via a phone call to the squad, adding a political subplot to a high-profile opener between the hosts and returning South Americans.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/fifa-world-cup/paraguays-president-will-be-at-usas-fifa-world-cup-2026-opener-but-is-donald-trump-attending/articleshow/131696028.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/fifa-world-cup/paraguays-president-will-be-at-usas-fifa-world-cup-2026-opener-but-is-donald-trump-attending/articleshow/131696028.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-13T06:28:54+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Sports Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131696039,imgsize-61356.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Trump's message to USNMT revealed as president calls squad before FIFA World Cup 2026 opener against Paraguay]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131695909.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[The United States received a morale boost ahead of its 2026 FIFA World Cup opener after President Donald Trump personally called the squad to wish them luck. Speaking with head coach Mauricio Pochettino and captain Tim Ream, Trump backed the team's chances on home soil as preparations intensified for the clash with Paraguay, adding to the growing anticipation surrounding the hosts' tournament debut.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/fifa-world-cup/trumps-message-to-usnmt-revealed-as-president-calls-squad-before-fifa-world-cup-2026-opener-against-paraguay/articleshow/131695909.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/fifa-world-cup/trumps-message-to-usnmt-revealed-as-president-calls-squad-before-fifa-world-cup-2026-opener-against-paraguay/articleshow/131695909.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-13T05:56:22+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131695912,imgsize-56812.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why did Clavicular get so emotional? Looksmaxxing streamer faces intense reactions during recovery stream]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/131695717.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Kick streamer Braden Peters, better known as Clavicular, went viral after becoming emotional during a livestream while recovering from facial surgery. The moment happened during his “Ascension Week” content series when a text-to-speech donation criticized his appearance. The clip sparked debate about cosmetic procedures, online criticism, and the growing influence of looksmaxxing content among young audiences.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/why-did-clavicular-get-so-emotional-looksmaxxing-streamer-faces-intense-reactions-during-recovery-stream/articleshow/131695717.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/why-did-clavicular-get-so-emotional-looksmaxxing-streamer-faces-intense-reactions-during-recovery-stream/articleshow/131695717.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-13T04:54:15+05:30</pubDate><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-131695714,imgsize-18458.cms"/></item></channel></rss>